<div class="search-tips">
    <h3>Search tips</h3>
    <ul class="bulleted">
        <li>Combine keywords and attributes to find specific items.
            <ul class="example">
                <li>morrison beloved</li>
                <li>Egypt foreign relations</li>
            </ul></li>
        <li>Use quotation marks to search as a phrase.
            <ul class="example">
                <li>"free market"</li>
                <li>"mourning becomes electra"</li>
            </ul></li>
        <li>Use "+" before a term to make it required. (Otherwise results matching only some of your terms may be included).
            <ul class="example">
                <li>+cuba +politics</li>
            </ul></li>
        <li>Use "-" before a word or phrase to exclude.
            <ul class="example">
                <li>jaguar -car -automobiles</li>
            </ul></li>
        <li>Use "OR", "AND", and "NOT" to create complex boolean logic. You can use parentheses in your complex expressions.
            <ul class="example">
                <li>paul AND auster</li>
            </ul></li>
        <li>Truncation and wildcards are not supported - word-stemming is done automatically.</li>
    </ul>
</div>